verses.text: Give ear , O ye heavens , and I will speak ; and hear , O earth , the words of my mouth.
My doctrine shall drop as the rain , my speech shall distil as the dew , as the small rain upon the tender herb , and as the showers upon the grass :
Because I will publish the name of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: ascribe ye greatness unto our God.
\add He is\add* the Rock , his work \add is\add* perfect : for all his ways \add are\add* judgment : a God of truth and without iniquity , just and right \add is\add* he.

They have corrupted themselves, their spot \add is\add* not \add the spot\add* of his children : \add they are\add* a perverse and crooked generation.\f + \fr 32.5 \ft They have…: Heb. He hath corrupted to himself\f*\f + \fr 32.5 \ft their…: or, that they are not his children, that is their blot\f*

Do ye thus requite the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, O foolish people and unwise ? \add is\add* not he thy father \add that\add* hath bought thee? hath he not made thee, and established thee? \p

¶ Remember the days of old , consider the years of many generations : ask thy father , and he will shew thee; thy elders , and they will tell thee.\f + \fr 32.7 \ft many…: Heb. generation and generation\f*
When the most High divided to the nations their inheritance , when he separated the sons of Adam , he set the bounds of the people according to the number of the children of Israel.
For the \nd \+w LORD’s|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* portion \add is\add* his people ; Jacob \add is\add* the lot of his inheritance.\f + \fr 32.9 \ft lot: Heb. cord\f*
He found him in a desert land , and in the waste howling wilderness ; he led him about , he instructed him, he kept him as the apple of his eye.\f + \fr 32.10 \ft led: or, compassed\f*
As an eagle stirreth up her nest , fluttereth over her young , spreadeth abroad her wings , taketh them, beareth them on her wings :
\add So\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* alone did lead him, and \add there was\add* no strange god with him.
He made him ride on the high places of the earth , that he might eat the increase of the fields ; and he made him to suck honey out of the rock , and oil out of the flinty rock ;
Butter of kine , and milk of sheep , with fat of lambs , and rams of the breed of Bashan , and goats , with the fat of kidneys of wheat ; and thou didst drink the pure blood of the grape. \p

¶ But Jeshurun waxed fat , and kicked : thou art waxen fat , thou art grown thick , thou art covered \add with fatness;\add* then he forsook God \add which\add* made him, and lightly esteemed the Rock of his salvation.
They provoked him to jealousy with strange \add gods\add*, with abominations provoked they him to anger.
They sacrificed unto devils , not to God ; to gods whom they knew not, to new \add gods that\add* came newly up , whom your fathers feared not.\f + \fr 32.17 \ft not to…: or, which were not God\f*
Of the Rock \add that\add* begat thee thou art unmindful , and hast forgotten God that formed thee. \p
And when the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* saw \add it\add*, he abhorred \add them\add*, because of the provoking of his sons , and of his daughters.\f + \fr 32.19 \ft abhorred: or, despised\f*
And he said , I will hide my face from them, I will see what their end \add shall be:\add* for they \add are\add* a very froward generation , children in whom \add is\add* no faith.

They have moved me to jealousy with \add that which is\add* not God ; they have provoked me to anger with their vanities : and I will move them to jealousy with \add those which are\add* not a people ; I will provoke them to anger with a foolish nation.

For a fire is kindled in mine anger , and shall burn unto the lowest hell , and shall consume the earth with her increase , and set on fire the foundations of the mountains.\f + \fr 32.22 \ft shall burn: or, hath burned\f*\f + \fr 32.22 \ft shall consume: or, hath consumed\f*
I will heap mischiefs upon them; I will spend mine arrows upon them.

\add They shall be\add* burnt with hunger , and devoured with burning heat , and with bitter destruction : I will also send the teeth of beasts upon them, with the poison of serpents of the dust.\f + \fr 32.24 \ft heat: Heb. coals\f*

The sword without , and terror within , shall destroy both the young man and the virgin , the suckling \add also\add* with the man of gray hairs.\f + \fr 32.25 \ft within: Heb. from the chambers\f*\f + \fr 32.25 \ft destroy: Heb. bereave\f* \p
I said , I would scatter them into corners , I would make the remembrance of them to cease from among men :

Were it not that I feared the wrath of the enemy , lest their adversaries should behave themselves strangely , \add and\add* lest they should say , Our hand \add is\add* high , and the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath not done all this.\f + \fr 32.27 \ft Our…: or, Our high hand, and not the \+nd LORD\+nd* hath done\f*
For they \add are\add* a nation void of counsel , neither \add is there any\add* understanding in them.
O that they were wise , \add that\add* they understood this, \add that\add* they would consider their latter end !
How should one chase a thousand , and two put ten thousand to flight , except their Rock had sold them , and the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had shut them up ?
For their rock \add is\add* not as our Rock , even our enemies themselves \add being\add* judges.

For their vine \add is\add* of the vine of Sodom , and of the fields of Gomorrah : their grapes \add are\add* grapes of gall , their clusters \add are\add* bitter :\f + \fr 32.32 \ft of the vine: or, worse than the vine\f*
Their wine \add is\add* the poison of dragons , and the cruel venom of asps.
\add Is\add* not this laid up in store with me, \add and\add* sealed up among my treasures ?

To me \add belongeth\add* vengeance , and recompence ; their foot shall slide in \add due\add* time : for the day of their calamity \add is\add* at hand , and the things that shall come upon them make haste.

For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* shall judge his people , and repent himself for his servants , when he seeth that \add their\add* power is gone , and \add there is\add* none shut up , or left.\f + \fr 32.36 \ft power: Heb. hand\f*
And he shall say , Where \add are\add* their gods , \add their\add* rock in whom they trusted ,

Which did eat the fat of their sacrifices , \add and\add* drank the wine of their drink offerings ? let them rise up and help you, \add and\add* be your protection.\f + \fr 32.38 \ft your…: Heb. an hiding for you\f* \p

See now that I, \add even\add* I, \add am\add* he, and \add there is\add* no god with me: I kill , and I make alive ; I wound , and I heal : neither \add is there any\add* that can deliver out of my hand.
For I lift up my hand to heaven , and say , I live for ever.
If I whet my glittering sword , and mine hand take hold on judgment ; I will render vengeance to mine enemies , and will reward them that hate me.
I will make mine arrows drunk with blood , and my sword shall devour flesh ; \add and that\add* with the blood of the slain and of the captives , from the beginning of revenges upon the enemy.

Rejoice , O ye nations , \add with\add* his people : for he will avenge the blood of his servants , and will render vengeance to his adversaries , and will be merciful unto his land , \add and\add* to his people.\f + \fr 32.43 \ft Rejoice…: or, Praise his people, ye nations: or, Sing ye\f* \p
¶ And Moses came and spake all the words of this song in the ears of the people , he, and Hoshea the son of Nun.\f + \fr 32.44 \ft Hoshea: or, Joshua\f*
And Moses made an end of speaking all these words to all Israel :
And he said unto them, Set your hearts unto all the words which I testify among you this day , which ye shall command your children to observe to do , all the words of this law.
For it \add is\add* not a vain thing for you; because it \add is\add* your life : and through this thing ye shall prolong \add your\add* days in the land , whither ye go over Jordan to possess it.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses that selfsame day , saying ,

Get thee up into this mountain Abarim , \add unto\add* mount Nebo , which \add is\add* in the land of Moab , that \add is\add* over against Jericho ; and behold the land of Canaan , which I give unto the children of Israel for a possession :
And die in the mount whither thou goest up , and be gathered unto thy people ; as Aaron thy brother died in mount Hor , and was gathered unto his people :

Because ye trespassed against me among the children of Israel at the waters of Meribah-Kadesh , in the wilderness of Zin ; because ye sanctified me not in the midst of the children of Israel.\f + \fr 32.51 \ft Meribah-Kadesh: or, strife at Kadesh\f*
Yet thou shalt see the land before \add thee;\add* but thou shalt not go thither unto the land which I give the children of Israel.
